The Zoning Resolution of the City of New York, effective as of December 15, 1961, and as subsequently amended, is further amended by changing the Zoning Map, Section No. 22d: 

1.       changing from an existing C8-2 District to an R6A District property bounded by a line 75 feet northeasterly of 92nd Street, a line 125 feet northwesterly of 5th Avenue, 92nd Street, and a line 185 feet northwesterly of 5th Avenue; 


12.     changing from an existing C8-2 District to an R7A District property bounded by a line 85 feet southwesterly of 91st Street, 5th Avenue, 92nd Street, a line 185 feet northwesterly of 5th Avenue, a line 75 feet northeasterly of 92nd Street, and a line 125 feet northwesterly of 5th Avenue; and 

3.         establishing within a proposed R6A District a C2-4 District bounded by a line 75 feet northeasterly of 92nd Street, a line 125 feet northwesterly of 5th Avenue, 92nd Street, and a line 185 feet northwesterly of 5th Avenue; and 


24.      establishing within a proposed R7A District a C2-4 District bounded by a line 85 feet southwesterly of 91st Street, 5th Avenue, 92nd Street, a line 185 feet northwesterly of 5th Avenue, a line 75 feet northeasterly of 92nd Street, and a line 125 feet northwesterly of 5th Avenue; 

as shown on a diagram (for illustrative purposes only) dated September 14, 2020, and subject to the conditions of CEQR Declaration E-577.

Adopted.

